Model building¶

Smote¶

Now we see that the datais imbalanced. So our model will be biased so we need to balance the data to train is properly. So we'll apply SMOTE to train Data.

In [64]:
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
In [65]:
sm = SMOTE(random_state = 3)
In [66]:
OversampledX, OversampledY = sm.fit_resample(X_new, Y)
In [67]:
## Checking the data is balance or not after SMOTE
OversampledY.value_counts(normalize = True)

Decision Tree classifier

In [71]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
decision_tree = DecisionTreeClassifier()

Here we are using HalvingGridSerchCV instead of GriDSearchCV becuse the execution time of HalvingGridSearchCV is 25 time less that normal GridSearchCV.

In [72]:
